modules.description: This module implements the Salsa20 core functions with 8, 12, and 20 rounds, each taking a 64-byte input string (16 blocks of 32 bits) and producing a 64-byte output string. These functions perform cryptographic transformations used in the Salsa20 stream cipher for generating keystreams. They are specifically designed for encryption applications requiring high-speed, secure pseudorandom data generation.
